# Codegen And Generated Output Quality

Generated files under `packages/extension/demos/generated/` must be **lint- and typecheck-clean without ESLint `--fix`**. Fix the generator templates, not the committed output.

**Always:** do not hand-edit `packages/extension/demos/generated/**` or bundled MCP files to fix behavior — see [generated-output-do-not-edit.mdc](./generated-output-do-not-edit.mdc).

## When this applies

Changes under `packages/cli/src/generator/` (or other generator wiring that affects `*-tools.ts` output).

## Required verification

From the **db2ai workspace root**, run in order:

1. `npm run build`
2. `npm run generate:all`
3. `npm run build:generated --prefix packages/extension/demos`
4. `npm run check`

Do **not** run `eslint --fix` on generated files to “repair” output. If `check` fails, fix the generator and regenerate.

Optional: run `npm run format` if you want Prettier-applied output before commit.

## What root `check` covers

- `format:check` — Prettier on hand-written `.ts` and demo `packages/extension/demos/generated/**/*.ts` (Langium `packages/language/src/generated/` excluded)
- `typecheck` — workspace `tsc -b` plus demo generated `.ts`
- `lint` — ESLint on hand-written `.ts`, demo `generated/**`, and auth stubs (Langium `packages/language/src/generated/**` excluded)

## Langium output

`packages/language/src/generated/**` is excluded from Prettier, ESLint, and type-check (`// @ts-nocheck` after `langium:generate`). Do not fix Langium output by hand.

## Commit generated output

When demo `.db2ai` files or generator output shape change, include regenerated `packages/extension/demos/generated/**/*.ts` and emitted `.js` (plus `.map` if tracked) in the same change set. See [demos-build-generated.mdc](./demos-build-generated.mdc).
